! $Id: strftime,v 1.1 2001/12/07 16:54:19 toast Exp $
STRFTIME(time format)
  Returns a string representing the time with the given format.
  The format string may contain one or more conversion specifications,
  represented by a percent sign (%) followed by another character.

  NOTE: Supported conversion specifications may depend on your operating
	system or compiler.  See the strftime(3) man page or similar
	documentation for more information.

Examples:
  strftime(777 %H:%M)		- Returns "18:12"
  strftime($time() %D)		- Returns "12/02/01"

See also:
  FUNCTIONS TIME
  FUNCTIONS STIME
